TextChange: Being a good person would surely make one happy as well, right?  => S

Remembering a discussion in my ethics class back in uni which focused on what the best choice is to bring about \"good,\" it centered on doing what brings about the best results for the greatest number of people. Similar to calculating happiness, though, I realized that what is good for me is sometimes not what is good, or happiness-causing for the next person. But I was still someone worth making happy. And sometimes what is best for others reduces my happiness, such as having contact with an abuser or energy vampire. After that discussion, I abandoned my upbringing that my job was to always do what made others happy. It matters what makes me happy -- or not.  \n\nIt was during that discussion though that I realized sometimes what is good for one depletes from another.  => I
